Useful to :

INSTRING2
---------

- Develop a text-based command assistant,
- or running a custom font,
- ...

ISSTRING ( originally written for OS2 )
--------

Check in RAM that the argument is a string.

Important For Basic-Devs :
Prgm(Your_Argument)
Argument = 'Local' VAR -> so in RAM

(For declared variables, prefer 'getType()')


Note :
------
By renaming & using getType() right away STR is exposed in the Var-Link Menu.

If your classmate has physical access to your calculator, this can also affect your personal programs !

So

In order to preserve the contents of the STR variable, it may be useful to process variables in RAM.


